  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6585.65 trading just below the GEX flip at 6590, dealers are positioned long gamma and will provide stabilizing flow - selling any push toward the massive 6600 gamma wall (57B) and buying dips toward 6560 support. The recent wall break and GEX surge (25%+ in 1-5 minutes) suggests volatility is spiking but the PIN regime should contain moves within the 6560-6600 range as dealers hedge dynamically. Key levels: watch for dealer selling pressure into 6590-6600 resistance cluster and buying support at 6585 then 6560.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6560 and 6600 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
